      "date": "2017-04-24 04:29:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nPlease have a look at these files: lustre/utils/obdfilter-survey.sh and lustre-iokit/obdfilter-survey/*.obdfilter-survey. Actually, the \"case='network'\" does only support single IP/hostname.\nIf you want to support multiple IP/hostnames in test, you should improve some functions in files lustre-iokit/obdfilter-survey/{obdfilter-survey, iokit-libecho}, but not obdfilter-survey.sh.\nYou current fix is not correct, because in my test it showed targets=\"\".",
